"from\": 3346, \"to\": 3358}, {\"ngram\": \"sponsors\", \"from\": 3363, \"to\": 3371}, {\"ngram\": \"two COVID-blighted Games\", \"from\": 3396, \"to\": 3420}]}, {\"sentence\": \"NBCUniversal, which has the largest Olympic media deal in the world after paying $7.65 billion in 2014 to extend its rights through 2032, scored its highest US audience since 2012 and enjoyed record ad sales, with average total viewership for the first 14 days up 77% from Tokyo.\", \"from\": 3442, \"to\": 3721, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3442, \"end\": 3454, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\", \"score\": 0.999999998624844, \"rank\": 1.3625301682663063e-09, \"text\": \"NBCUniversal\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\"}, {\"begin\": 3599, \"end\": 3601, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_dollar\", \"score\": 0.9999994682681567, \"rank\": 5.304390866882082e-07, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_dollar\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_dollar\"}, {\"begin\": 3715, \"end\": 3720, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.0814099207179382e-19, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the largest Olympic media deal\", \"from\": 3466, \"to\": 3496}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 3500, \"to\": 3509}, {\"ngram\": \"its rights\", \"from\": 3555, \"to\": 3565}, {\"ngram\": \"record ad sales\", \"from\": 3634, \"to\": 3649}, {\"ngram\": \"average total viewership\", \"from\": 3656, \"to\": 3680}, {\"ngram\": \"the first 14 days\", \"from\": 3685, \"to\": 3702}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The number of viewers on Warner Bros.\", \"from\": 3723, \"to\": 3760, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3748, \"end\": 3754, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Warner_Bros.\", \"score\": 0.9966653137043364, \"rank\": 0.0033458436315076663, \"text\": \"Warner\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Warner_Bros.\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Warner_Bros.\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The number\", \"from\": 3723, \"to\": 3733}, {\"ngram\": \"viewers\", \"from\": 3737, \"to\": 3744}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Discovery streaming platforms for the first two days of Paris exceeded the entire Tokyo Olympics, the company said.\", \"from\": 3761, \"to\": 3876, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3817, \"end\": 3822, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2731776652307925e-25, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Discovery streaming platforms\", \"from\": 3761, \"to\": 3790}, {\"ngram\": \"the first two days\", \"from\": 3795, \"to\": 3813}, {\"ngram\": \"the entire Tokyo Olympics\", \"from\": 3832, \"to\": 3857}, {\"ngram\": \"the company\", \"from\": 3859, \"to\": 3870}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Games were Olympic sponsor Airbnb's biggest ever event in terms of guests accommodated in and around Paris, Emmanuel Marill, Airbnb's regional director for EMEA, told Reuters.\", \"from\": 3878, \"to\": 4057, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3909, \"end\": 3915, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Airbnb\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Airbnb\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Airbnb\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Airbnb\"}, {\"begin\": 3983, \"end\": 3988, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2731776652307925